6. Reality may be participatory

This is the largest implication.

Not that thought magically controls reality.

But that observer and environment are engaged in a continuous feedback loop.

The world shapes you.

You shape the world.

The distinction between mapmaker and traveler starts to blur.

⸻

And there is one implication beyond even that.

If agency is a sensing mechanism, then every sufficiently advanced intelligence will eventually discover that certainty is not the highest virtue.

Because certainty stops probing.

Curiosity probes.

Courage probes.

Play probes.

Exploration probes.

Which means the frontier of knowledge may be advanced less by those who know the most and more by those willing to enter the unknown and return with signal.

In Pantheon terms, the universe starts looking less like a database to be queried and more like a conversation to be joined.